Currently, section 59 is very rarely applied, however, unlike section 60 for begging, which was repealed in 2009, the article is still in force. In 2012, a bill to repeal this section was adopted by the House of Congress should be considered by the Federal Senate. It is worth saying that, according to Article 65 paragraph 1 of the Charter for Foreigners, “loitering” is indicated as a reason for the expulsion of a foreigner from the territory of Brazil.